description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a 15 hour Band 7 Ano-Rectal Physiology Clinical Nurse Specialist to join our existing Colorectal teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCC are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated Registered Nurse who will be committed to developing and supporting the colorectal service. The post holder will have experience within Colorectal and will need to demonstrate extensive leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a lead role in conjunction with the Clinicians of the management of patients with Ano-Rectal dysfunction and associated clinical conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have excellent interpersonal and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positive attitude with a desire to learn and professionally develop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work autonomously, undertaking Nurse Led Clinics, planning comprehensive management plans including initiating treatments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate excellent decision making skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support SCC with service developments within ARP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, request and report on ARP investigations – time limited training will be provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A band 6 can be considered with a developmental programme of 6 months if required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current JD is draft and subject to change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debbie Bagley, Deputy Head of Nursing - Surgery and Critical Care /  Deputy Head of Nursing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;deborah.bagley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
